# ovh_cloud_storage_object_bucket_object_versions (Data Source)

Lists versions (and delete markers) of a single S3 object using the v2 API. The response is a single page controlled by `limit`, `key_marker` and `version_id_marker`; follow `next_key_marker` / `next_version_id_marker` to fetch subsequent pages.

## Example Usage

{{tffile "examples/data-sources/ovh_cloud_storage_object_bucket_object_versions/data-source.tf"}}

## Schema

### Required

- `bucket_name` (String) Name of the bucket
- `object_key` (String) Object key whose versions to list
- `service_name` (String) Service name of the resource representing the id of the cloud project

### Optional

- `key_marker` (String) Key to resume listing from
- `limit` (Number) Maximum number of entries to return (API hard cap: 1000)
- `version_id_marker` (String) Version ID to resume listing from (must be paired with `key_marker`)

### Read-Only

- `is_truncated` (Boolean) Whether more versions exist beyond the current page
- `next_key_marker` (String) Key to pass as `key_marker` for the next page; empty when `is_truncated` is false
- `next_version_id_marker` (String) Version ID to pass as `version_id_marker` for the next page; empty when `is_truncated` is false
- `objects` (Attributes List) Object versions and delete markers returned for the current page

Each element of `objects` exposes the same fields as the single-object data source `ovh_cloud_storage_object_bucket_object`.
